Appendix B: Computational Specifications

B.1 CBF-QP Solver Pseudocode

```
Algorithm: Fixed-Iteration Primal-Dual Interior Point QP for CBF Filter

Input: State estimate x_hat, desired control u_des, constraint matrices A, b
Output: Safe control u_safe

Parameters:
    k_max = 20           // Fixed iterations for WCET
    mu = 10              // Barrier parameter initial
    sigma = 0.1          // Centering parameter
    tol = 1e-6           // Not used for termination, only for residual check

Initialize:
    u = u_des            // Primal variable
    lambda = zeros(m)    // Dual variables (constraints)
    s = ones(m)          // Slack variables
    mu_current = mu

For iter = 1 to k_max:
    // Compute residuals
    r_dual = H * (u - u_des) + A^T * lambda
    r_cent = -diag(lambda) * s - mu_current
    r_pri = A * u - b + s

    // Solve KKT system
    Form KKT matrix K = [ H, A^T; A, -diag(lambda)^-1 * diag(s) ]
    Solve K * [du; dlambda] = -[r_dual; r_pri + diag(lambda)^-1 * r_cent]

    // Recover ds
    ds = -diag(lambda)^-1 * (r_cent + diag(s) * dlambda)

    // Line search (fixed fraction to avoid branching)
    alpha = 0.95 * min(1, min_{i: dlambda_i < 0} (-lambda_i / dlambda_i))
    alpha = min(alpha, min_{i: ds_i < 0} (-s_i / ds_i))

    // Update
    u = u + alpha * du
    lambda = lambda + alpha * dlambda
    s = s + alpha * ds

    // Update barrier parameter
    mu_current = sigma * (lambda^T * s) / m

Return u
```

