C.2 Confidence Bound Calculation

For $N = 10,000$ samples with zero constraint violations observed, the Clopper-Pearson exact binomial confidence interval upper bound for violation probability $\epsilon$ at 95% confidence is:

\epsilon \le 1 - (0.05)^{1/N} \approx \frac{\ln(20)}{N} = \frac{2.996}{10,000} = 3.0 \times 10^{-4} 

This meets the preliminary human-rating target of $\epsilon \le 10^{-3}$ for conceptual design phase.

C.3 Landing Dispersion Ellipse Computation

Given landing points $(x_i, y_i)_{i=1}^N$ in local tangent plane coordinates:

1. Compute sample mean: $\bar{x} = \frac{1}{N} \sum x_i$, $\bar{y} = \frac{1}{N} \sum y_i$
2. Compute sample covariance:
   \Sigma = \frac{1}{N-1} \sum_{i=1}^N \begin{bmatrix} (x_i - \bar{x})^2 & (x_i - \bar{x})(y_i - \bar{y}) \\ (y_i - \bar{y})(x_i - \bar{x}) & (y_i - \bar{y})^2 \end{bmatrix} 
3. Eigenvalue decomposition: $\Sigma = V \Lambda V^T$, $\Lambda = \text{diag}(\lambda_1, \lambda_2)$
4. The $3\sigma$ dispersion ellipse has semi-major axis $a = 3\sqrt{\lambda_1}$ and semi-minor axis $b = 3\sqrt{\lambda_2}$.

For the ADIC adaptive guidance, typical results yield $\lambda_1 \approx 900$ m², $\lambda_2 \approx 400$ m², giving $a \approx 90$ m, $b \approx 60$ m, satisfying the $D_{3\sigma} \le 100$ m objective.

